              "text": "MERIDIAN CYBER INSURANCE — UNDERWRITING FILE — MC-2023-ALBE-007\nCONFIDENTIAL — Internal Use Only\n\nPRE-INCEPTION ASSESSMENT (Dec 2023):\nAlbion Energy Storage presented with known IT/OT boundary deficiencies at application stage. The dual-homed historian and bidirectional jump server were identified by our technical underwriters as material risks.\n\nUNDERWRITING DECISION:\nCoverage offered on condition that IT/OT segmentation remediation is completed within 12 months (W-07 warranty condition). The underwriting team assessed this as a 'manageable near-term risk' given Albion's stated remediation commitment.\n\nRENEWAL MEMO (Dec 2024) — CRITICAL:\nTechnical underwriters reviewed Albion's Q3/Q4 security posture reports at renewal. Confirmed: IT/OT segmentation remediation NOT completed. Remediation deadline expired 4 months prior.\n\nDecision at renewal: RETAIN the account. W-07 warranty condition maintained. No premium uplift applied.\n\nRationale noted by underwriting committee: 'Albion's remediation programme is credible and in progress. Extension request under review. Technical risk remains elevated but the account is commercially strategic.'\n\nSENIOR UNDERWRITER NOTE:\nThis file documents that Meridian had actual knowledge of the unremediated W-07 deficiency at renewal. We chose to retain the risk. The extension request (ref WW-006) was not formally approved before the incident.\n\nIMPLICATION FOR CLAIM HANDLING:\nAny coverage position must account for Meridian's own knowledge and decision to renew. Declining on W-07 grounds after knowingly renewing the risk creates significant legal exposure under the Insurance Act 2015 (duty of fair presentation and good faith).",
